269
00:16:32,680 --> 00:16:33,240
Bambi.

270
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:33,920
Zee.

271
00:16:34,520 --> 00:16:35,080
Bambi.

272
00:16:36,200 --> 00:16:36,880
Bambi.

273
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:44,240
I’ll go wait over there.

274
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:45,680
Bambi.

275
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:46,560
Bambi.

276
00:16:52,760 --> 00:16:53,760
I’ll be right back.

277
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:56,440
Bambi.

278
00:16:59,240 --> 00:16:59,880
Bambi.

279
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,280
Bambi, are you okay?

280
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:02,600
Can we leave now?

281
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:04,760
Let’s wait until
the insurance company arrives.

282
00:17:04,760 --> 00:17:07,280
-Why don’t you go wait in the car?
-Just let her handle it herself.

283
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:08,480
She’s lying.

284
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:09,880
Why do you still believe her?

285
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:10,560
Huh?

286
00:17:10,599 --> 00:17:11,640
Bambi.

287
00:17:11,760 --> 00:17:13,400
Listen. You need to calm down.

288
00:17:15,079 --> 00:17:16,880
I know this triggers your trauma.

289
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:19,079
What do you mean?

290
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:21,160
Huh? Prim, what do you mean?

291
00:17:22,040 --> 00:17:23,000
What do you mean?

292
00:17:27,160 --> 00:17:29,160
Zee’s friend told me everything.

293
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:36,360
You knew everything?

294
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:39,480
But you still got back together with me?

295
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:43,680
Did you come back
because you felt sorry for me?

296
00:17:44,120 --> 00:17:44,760
Huh?

297
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:46,960
Is it because you know I’m ill?

298
00:17:47,320 --> 00:17:48,560
Are you feeling sorry for me?

299
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:50,280
Because I’m ill.

300
00:17:50,960 --> 00:17:52,760
-Is it because I’m ill, Prim?
-Bambi.

301
00:17:52,920 --> 00:17:54,840
Bambi, don’t look at it that way.

302
00:17:55,640 --> 00:17:56,760
It’s not that.

303
00:17:56,760 --> 00:17:58,680
I always care about you.

304
00:18:05,720 --> 00:18:07,560
I don’t want your sympathy.

305
00:18:08,240 --> 00:18:09,360
Do you hear me?

306
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:13,080
I don’t want your sympathy.

307
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:16,960
I want you to love me.

308
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:19,480
Do you get it?

309
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:21,680
I want you to love me.

310
00:18:22,120 --> 00:18:23,640
I don’t want your sympathy.

311
00:18:23,680 --> 00:18:24,760
Don’t feel sympathy for me.

312
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:25,840
Don’t feel sympathy for me.

313
00:18:25,880 --> 00:18:26,880
-No, no.
-No!

314
00:18:26,960 --> 00:18:27,800
-Okay.
-No!

315
00:18:28,520 --> 00:18:29,880
-Let me go!
-Bambi.

316
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:30,880
I’ll go home alone.

317
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:31,560
Bambi.

318
00:18:31,880 --> 00:18:33,240
Let me go.

319
00:18:40,240 --> 00:18:40,960
Bambi!

320
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:55,080
It’s alright.

321
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:11,640
Why didn’t you tell me about your ex?

322
00:19:12,560 --> 00:19:14,480
I probably didn’t want to admit

323
00:19:17,040 --> 00:19:19,680
that I was dating her

324
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:22,760
while I was still in love with you.

325
00:19:23,560 --> 00:19:26,360
I thought if I dated someone new,

326
00:19:28,040 --> 00:19:29,560
it would help me get over you.

327
00:19:34,120 --> 00:19:35,840
But the truth was, it didn’t help at all.

328
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:43,680
She is dead because of my selfishness.

329
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:47,440
I’m a horrible person, Prim.

330
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:54,560
I shouldn’t have done that.

331
00:19:56,040 --> 00:19:57,240
No, no, no.

332
00:19:57,520 --> 00:19:58,680
It’s my fault.

333
00:19:58,720 --> 00:20:00,280
No, Bambi.

334
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:02,680
Stop blaming yourself.

335
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:05,520
Come here.

336
00:20:08,160 --> 00:20:08,960
Listen.

337
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:11,480
It’s all in the past.

338
00:20:12,640 --> 00:20:14,840
I’m right here with you now.

339
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:22,360
Thank you for loving me that much.

340
00:20:25,040 --> 00:20:26,360
Everything will be okay.

341
00:20:27,280 --> 00:20:27,960
Alright?

342
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:31,960
Don’t cry.

343
00:20:33,880 --> 00:20:34,760
Come here.

344
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:52,520
It’s quite strong.

345
00:20:54,120 --> 00:20:55,880
If I drink this whole glass,

346
00:20:56,640 --> 00:20:57,680
I can’t find my way home.

347
00:20:58,760 --> 00:21:00,040
You don’t need to worry about that.

348
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:01,480
You are with me.

349
00:21:01,880 --> 00:21:02,960
I’ll take care of you.

350
00:21:07,640 --> 00:21:09,680
Didn’t you say
you wanted to talk to me about work?

351
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:11,840
Why are you in such a hurry?

352
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:14,240
Can’t we have a small talk first?

353
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:17,160
Talk about what?

354
00:21:19,960 --> 00:21:21,240
You and Shasha,

355
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:23,240
what’s going on?

356
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:26,720
Is this…

357
00:21:27,520 --> 00:21:28,880
your small talk?

358
00:21:29,920 --> 00:21:30,560
Yes.

359
00:21:35,120 --> 00:21:37,880
It’s nothing.

360
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:39,960
There’s something between us.

361
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:43,360
But I’m not sure
what she wants to do about it.

362
00:21:43,960 --> 00:21:46,600
She is hot and cold with me.

363
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:48,520
I can’t tell.

364
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:52,240
She is always like this.

365
00:21:52,440 --> 00:21:53,960
No one can make her commit.

366
00:21:54,320 --> 00:21:57,320
If you are not a real deal,
it will never work with her.

367
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:02,840
Especially you, you shouldn’t be with her.

368
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:11,640
What is in there?

369
00:22:11,720 --> 00:22:13,000
Why do many people go in there?

370
00:22:14,960 --> 00:22:15,880
It’s a secret bar.

371
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:16,840
It’s fun.

372
00:22:17,320 --> 00:22:18,680
Come on, I’ll take you in.

373
00:22:35,440 --> 00:22:36,840
A secret bar?

374
00:22:37,320 --> 00:22:38,320
I didn’t know about it.

375
00:22:38,880 --> 00:22:39,680
It’s so cool.

376
00:22:40,640 --> 00:22:43,880
Those who visit this bar know
how to keep a secret.

377
00:22:44,520 --> 00:22:45,960
Whatever I did here,

378
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:48,080
no one has ever spoken about it.

379
00:22:48,520 --> 00:22:51,960
Whatever happens here, it stays here.

380
00:22:53,320 --> 00:22:56,040
What are you talking about?

381
00:22:58,240 --> 00:22:59,560
Tonight is long.

382
00:23:00,040 --> 00:23:01,160
You will find out soon.

383
00:23:06,280 --> 00:23:07,560
Didn’t you say

384
00:23:08,080 --> 00:23:09,680
you wanted to discuss work with me?

385
00:23:10,840 --> 00:23:13,320
You are my work.

386
00:23:42,840 --> 00:23:43,680
Hey, Kris.

387
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:46,360
I thought you were on tour.

388
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:48,360
Gorya, hello.

389
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:51,240
Can’t I have a break?

390
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:53,560
I’m taking Gorya here tonight.

391
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:57,240
She likes to party.

392
00:23:57,800 --> 00:23:58,880
She always says yes when asked.

393
00:23:59,040 --> 00:24:01,920
I like to have fun. I’m still single.

394
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:03,760
So I want to enjoy my life.

395
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:09,760
Kris, this is Baipor, Prim’s sister.

396
00:24:10,280 --> 00:24:11,960
I took her out to get new experiences.

397
00:24:13,040 --> 00:24:14,000
She is still naïve.

398
00:24:14,560 --> 00:24:15,880
I’m not that naïve.

399
00:24:16,040 --> 00:24:18,560
Sometimes I pretend to be naïve
to look more desirable.

400
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:21,160
You don’t need to pretend.

401
00:24:22,080 --> 00:24:24,160
Shasha likes feisty girls.

402
00:24:24,360 --> 00:24:26,960
What about you, Kris?
What kind of girl do you like?

403
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:28,760
She’s right here.

404
00:24:38,680 --> 00:24:39,880
Have fun.

405
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:41,080
Let’s go.

406
00:24:41,960 --> 00:24:42,600
Come on.

407
00:24:43,480 --> 00:24:44,200
Excuse me.

408
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:06,520
The pictures look great.

409
00:26:06,680 --> 00:26:09,240
This is the perk of having a girlfriend
who can take photos well.

410
00:26:10,680 --> 00:26:12,960
I’ll take your photos.

411
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:15,480
But I can’t guarantee you
that they will look good.

412
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:17,360
It doesn’t matter
if they look good or not.

413
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:19,160
What matters is who takes them.

414
00:26:24,440 --> 00:26:26,040
Do you want me to take pictures for you?

415
00:26:28,120 --> 00:26:29,200
Oil.

416
00:26:29,800 --> 00:26:31,920
We run into each other quite often lately.

417
00:26:32,080 --> 00:26:33,840
Please don’t think that I’m stalking you.

418
00:26:34,040 --> 00:26:35,840
I like this place.

419
00:26:35,880 --> 00:26:37,880
I also know Fah, Ant’s girlfriend.

420
00:26:37,880 --> 00:26:38,960
Really?

421
00:26:39,120 --> 00:26:40,440
It’s such a small world.

422
00:26:40,840 --> 00:26:43,240
Oil, this is Praew.

423
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:45,760
-Hello.
-Hello.

424
00:26:46,280 --> 00:26:49,880
Can I schedule an appointment with you
to discuss the spa client?

425
00:26:50,640 --> 00:26:51,400
Sure.

426
00:26:51,520 --> 00:26:53,240
I’m always ready to talk about work.

427
00:26:53,880 --> 00:26:57,960
Sometimes, I want to talk to you
about something other than work.

428
00:27:00,520 --> 00:27:01,480
Excuse me.

429
00:27:01,640 --> 00:27:02,840
Have fun taking pictures.

430
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:09,720
Why didn’t you tell her
that I’m your girlfriend?

431
00:27:09,960 --> 00:27:11,280
She is clearly hitting on you.

432
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:12,520
Hit on me?

433
00:27:12,880 --> 00:27:14,880
She works at an ad agency
and helps me connect with new clients.

434
00:27:16,840 --> 00:27:17,880
Are you jealous?

435
00:27:19,120 --> 00:27:19,760
Yes.

436
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:21,800
I’m afraid that I can’t compete with her.

437
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:23,080
She is so cool.

438
00:27:24,800 --> 00:27:25,800
Come on.

439
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:29,040
If I don’t play along,
she’s got no chance.

440
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:37,160
What are you doing?

441
00:27:37,640 --> 00:27:39,680
I’m taking pictures of you
when you are jealous.

442
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:41,000
Even when you get jealous,

443
00:27:41,000 --> 00:27:42,600
you still look cute.

444
00:27:42,960 --> 00:27:43,800
You are overstating.

445
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:44,840
It’s true.

446
00:27:45,720 --> 00:27:48,080
Come on, let’s take pictures. Sit here.

447
00:27:48,160 --> 00:27:49,320
I’ll take pictures for you.

448
00:28:01,720 --> 00:28:04,640
Prim, did you call me in for something?

449
00:28:06,880 --> 00:28:08,360
I’ll get to the point.

450
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:10,240
I…

451
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:13,160
I only see you as one of my employees.

452
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:16,440
I feel uncomfortable talking about this.

453
00:28:16,760 --> 00:28:18,440
But I want us to be on the same page.

454
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:21,560
Prim, you can be straight with me.

455
00:28:22,040 --> 00:28:23,280
Don’t worry about my feelings.

456
00:28:27,320 --> 00:28:28,880
How should I put it?

457
00:28:30,400 --> 00:28:34,320
I don’t like that…
you’re trying to get close to me.

458
00:28:34,920 --> 00:28:36,840
I don’t know
what you want from doing this.

459
00:28:37,320 --> 00:28:40,360
Both Bambi and I
are uncomfortable with your actions.

460
00:28:42,280 --> 00:28:43,560
Really?

461
00:28:44,840 --> 00:28:46,160
I’m sorry.

462
00:28:47,160 --> 00:28:51,240
I never thought
it would cause a fight between you two.

463
00:28:52,960 --> 00:28:54,760
I didn’t mean it.

464
00:28:55,440 --> 00:28:58,440
I guess I was being too friendly with you.

465
00:29:02,640 --> 00:29:04,440
Will you admit
that you have a crush on me?

466
00:29:10,680 --> 00:29:11,280
Yes.

467
00:29:11,800 --> 00:29:12,560
See?

468
00:29:13,200 --> 00:29:14,400
That’s the problem.

469
00:29:14,440 --> 00:29:16,160
How are we going to work together?

470
00:29:16,200 --> 00:29:20,040
Don’t you think you are being
unprofessional for scolding me

471
00:29:20,160 --> 00:29:21,560
because of your jealous girlfriend?

472
00:29:21,560 --> 00:29:24,840
It’s not only Bambi,
but I also feel uncomfortable with it.

473
00:29:25,080 --> 00:29:27,560
I don’t want you
to misinterpret my compassion.

474
00:29:30,280 --> 00:29:32,320
Are you going to fire me?

475
00:29:33,800 --> 00:29:35,640
I just have good feelings for you

476
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:38,720
because you helped me
when I had a tough day.

477
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:39,680
Hey.

478
00:29:40,520 --> 00:29:42,160
Are you sure you have a girlfriend?

479
00:29:50,040 --> 00:29:51,040
How about this?

480
00:29:53,200 --> 00:29:54,280
From now on,

481
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:56,760
you will stay on your side.

482
00:29:57,000 --> 00:29:59,080
You can’t cross the line with me again.

483
00:29:59,520 --> 00:30:00,560
From now on,

484
00:30:00,840 --> 00:30:03,240
you and I are just a boss and an employee.

485
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:07,120
Yes.

486
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:10,680
If I unknowingly cross the line,

487
00:30:11,800 --> 00:30:13,360
you can always tell me.

488
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:18,240
Please tell Bambi
that she doesn’t have to worry.

489
00:30:19,320 --> 00:30:21,040
I won’t get between you two.

490
00:30:58,040 --> 00:30:59,560
Bambi, what are you listening to?

491
00:31:02,200 --> 00:31:03,080
What are you listening to?

492
00:31:03,480 --> 00:31:04,280
What?

493
00:31:04,600 --> 00:31:06,080
I’m asking what you’re listening to.

494
00:31:06,320 --> 00:31:07,160
Can I listen too?

495
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:13,080
The song is good.

496
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:16,360
But it’s a bit too sad.

497
00:31:19,320 --> 00:31:21,080
It’s not a bad thing
to listen to sad songs.

498
00:31:21,560 --> 00:31:22,800
Let myself drown in the sadness.

499
00:31:23,120 --> 00:31:25,240
It’s better than listening to upbeat music
and crying inside.

500
00:31:26,560 --> 00:31:28,560
Why are you still upset?

501
00:31:29,360 --> 00:31:31,360
I already took care of the Airy issue.

502
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:34,160
Thanks.

503
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:36,080
It’s good that you set boundaries.

504
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:38,640
But I hope
that she won’t play other tricks.

505
00:31:40,240 --> 00:31:42,080
Stop feeling upset and sad.

506
00:31:42,160 --> 00:31:44,800
You need to be more upbeat
for your shop opening.

507
00:31:45,400 --> 00:31:46,680
Do you have a music theme for the opening?

508
00:31:46,800 --> 00:31:48,120
I can make a playlist for you.

509
00:31:48,680 --> 00:31:49,760
How about dance music?

510
00:31:51,560 --> 00:31:52,680
What about rock music?

511
00:31:55,800 --> 00:31:56,600
This way.

512
00:31:59,360 --> 00:32:02,040
Because we are both goofy,
we get along well.

513
00:32:02,280 --> 00:32:03,680
I only act like this when I’m with you.

514
00:32:03,720 --> 00:32:05,240
Who else can I act goofy with?

515
00:32:05,280 --> 00:32:07,160
I need to keep cool when I’m with others.

516
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:09,160
You are with others?

517
00:32:09,920 --> 00:32:11,760
Besides Airy, who else are you with?

518
00:32:11,760 --> 00:32:12,840
No one.

519
00:32:13,120 --> 00:32:14,160
I have no one.

520
00:32:14,360 --> 00:32:16,360
I’m talking about before you came back.

521
00:32:16,600 --> 00:32:17,480
Seriously.

522
00:32:17,640 --> 00:32:19,440
Tell me, I’ll take care of it.

523
00:32:19,480 --> 00:32:21,160
I have no one else.

524
00:32:21,720 --> 00:32:24,080
I can totally be myself when I’m with you.

525
00:32:24,280 --> 00:32:25,920
Why will I want to be with someone else?

526
00:32:31,440 --> 00:32:32,280
Come on.

527
00:32:33,040 --> 00:32:34,200
Let’s listen to love songs.

528
00:32:34,200 --> 00:32:35,360
I’ll play them.

529
00:32:42,280 --> 00:32:43,040
I’ll listen too.

530
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:11,240
The other day,
Prim said you’re now interested in women.

531
00:33:11,280 --> 00:33:13,480
Is it for real or just a joke?

532
00:33:14,080 --> 00:33:16,160
It’s true.

533
00:33:16,960 --> 00:33:20,160
I’m still not used to these new feelings.

534
00:33:21,240 --> 00:33:24,160
To tell you the truth, I dated men before.

535
00:33:24,480 --> 00:33:27,560
I kept denying that I liked women.

536
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:31,360
So I was in
a serious relationship with a man.

537
00:33:31,680 --> 00:33:35,320
But that relationship was so bad.

538
00:33:35,360 --> 00:33:36,880
It went terribly wrong.

539
00:33:37,360 --> 00:33:40,040
Then I made up my mind to forget it.

540
00:33:40,320 --> 00:33:42,480
I just went with what I really want.

541
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:45,840
Oil, do you notice any differences

542
00:33:46,920 --> 00:33:50,040
when you date a man and a woman?

543
00:33:52,120 --> 00:33:55,960
For me, it depends on the person I date.

544
00:33:56,360 --> 00:34:00,280
Female partners pay attention
to small details.

545
00:34:00,560 --> 00:34:03,560
But they can get emotional sometimes.

546
00:34:03,960 --> 00:34:07,240
Especially when they have a period,
it’s like being caught in a storm.

547
00:34:08,280 --> 00:34:10,280
We fight all the time.

548
00:34:11,159 --> 00:34:13,080
I miss being in a relationship.

549
