00:51:15,240 --> 00:51:17,640
You can’t take responsibility
for everyone’s feelings.

826
00:51:18,160 --> 00:51:19,880
I think she has her reason.

827
00:51:22,120 --> 00:51:23,560
I just want to hear it from her.

828
00:51:37,120 --> 00:51:38,040
I’m sorry.

829
00:51:39,160 --> 00:51:39,960
Hey!

830
00:51:40,840 --> 00:51:42,040
How can you do that?

831
00:51:42,080 --> 00:51:43,160
It’s okay, Prim.

832
00:51:48,760 --> 00:51:50,440
You can hit me as many times as you want.

833
00:51:54,920 --> 00:51:56,680
If it’s going to make you forgive me.

834
00:52:00,720 --> 00:52:03,040
I didn’t know about you and Zee.

835
00:52:04,680 --> 00:52:06,480
Zee left me to be with you.

836
00:52:08,320 --> 00:52:09,680
She loved you very much.

837
00:52:11,560 --> 00:52:12,840
She did everything you asked.

838
00:52:14,280 --> 00:52:16,080
She gave everything to you.

839
00:52:17,920 --> 00:52:19,880
But you killed her.

840
00:52:22,200 --> 00:52:23,360
Look at you now.

841
00:52:24,080 --> 00:52:26,120
How dare you live a happy life like this?

842
00:52:27,800 --> 00:52:29,560
If you wanted to get back with Prim,

843
00:52:30,080 --> 00:52:31,800
then why did you date Zee?

844
00:52:32,840 --> 00:52:33,560
Wait.

845
00:52:35,440 --> 00:52:37,160
Airy, you know the truth?

846
00:52:37,880 --> 00:52:41,560
But you used AI to edit the audio clip
to make it sound like it was Bambi’s fault.

847
00:52:41,960 --> 00:52:43,480
You know that it was not her fault.

848
00:52:43,520 --> 00:52:45,640
But it was your ex’s fault.

849
00:52:53,120 --> 00:52:55,680
You can be mad and hate me.

850
00:52:57,920 --> 00:53:01,560
If I had listened to Zee
and not insisted on going to see Prim,

851
00:53:05,160 --> 00:53:06,840
Zee would still be here with you today.

852
00:53:09,040 --> 00:53:10,560
I’m sorry, Airy.

853
00:53:11,560 --> 00:53:12,960
Can you forgive me?

854
00:53:18,600 --> 00:53:20,360
Do you think it’s that easy?

855
00:53:22,480 --> 00:53:23,760
I know it’s hard.

856
00:53:24,440 --> 00:53:27,160
I’ve been living
with the guilt all this time.

857
00:53:29,600 --> 00:53:32,640
But I can’t punish myself
more than I already did, Airy.

858
00:53:34,680 --> 00:53:36,760
We have to move on with our lives.

859
00:54:23,440 --> 00:54:25,760
I’m sorry, Airy. I’m sorry.

860
00:54:29,880 --> 00:54:31,480
I’m really sorry, Airy.

861
00:54:34,920 --> 00:54:36,480
I didn’t mean it.

862
00:54:38,040 --> 00:54:39,560
I’m sorry.

863
00:54:43,280 --> 00:54:45,680
Please forgive me, Airy.

864
00:54:48,120 --> 00:54:49,160
I’m sorry.

865
00:54:51,280 --> 00:54:52,680
I’m sorry.

866
00:54:53,240 --> 00:54:54,760
I’m sorry.

867
00:54:58,080 --> 00:54:59,520
I’m sorry.

868
00:55:06,000 --> 00:55:08,560
I’m sorry.

869
00:55:22,400 --> 00:55:23,160
Prim.

870
00:55:30,240 --> 00:55:31,880
Shasha called me.

871
00:55:32,360 --> 00:55:34,080
She said she wanted to
come to see you, too.

872
00:55:34,160 --> 00:55:35,960
Everyone is worried about you.

873
00:55:37,320 --> 00:55:39,000
I called Bambi, but she didn’t answer.

874
00:55:39,600 --> 00:55:40,840
I’m worried about both of you.

875
00:55:41,160 --> 00:55:43,360
We need to give her some space.

876
00:55:48,800 --> 00:55:49,720
What about you?

877
00:55:51,240 --> 00:55:52,760
Is there anything I can do for you?

878
00:55:54,040 --> 00:55:55,760
There’s nothing you can do for me.

879
00:55:59,480 --> 00:56:00,760
I feel bad for her.

880
00:56:02,360 --> 00:56:03,960
I still feel guilty.

881
00:56:04,480 --> 00:56:07,200
I’m one of the reasons
why she ends up like this.

882
00:56:07,880 --> 00:56:09,160
Stop blaming yourself.

883
00:56:10,560 --> 00:56:12,560
Bambi chose to leave you.

884
00:56:12,880 --> 00:56:14,560
Everything that happened after that,

885
00:56:14,880 --> 00:56:16,360
it’s not your fault.

886
00:56:29,840 --> 00:56:31,440
Bambi will be alright.

887
00:56:32,360 --> 00:56:33,840
Stop worrying too much.

888
00:56:35,840 --> 00:56:38,800
If you keep comforting me like this,
I don’t think I can hold it in.

889
00:56:38,840 --> 00:56:40,160
I’m going to cry again.

890
00:56:42,360 --> 00:56:42,960
Prim.

891
00:56:50,720 --> 00:56:51,640
Thank you.

892
00:57:01,080 --> 00:57:02,680
Do you remember the project in Phuket?

893
00:57:02,680 --> 00:57:04,360
The client wants to move the shooting up.

894
00:57:04,680 --> 00:57:05,880
I can’t take this job.

895
00:57:06,200 --> 00:57:08,040
(You know what’s going on with Bambi.)

896
00:57:08,600 --> 00:57:10,280
Min won’t be mad at you
because of this, right?

897
00:57:10,440 --> 00:57:12,240
Min can handle it. Don’t worry.

898
00:57:12,640 --> 00:57:13,560
Surprise.

899
00:57:14,320 --> 00:57:15,080
Wow.

900
00:57:15,640 --> 00:57:18,560
It’s a basic romantic gesture.

901
00:57:18,760 --> 00:57:20,760
Watch the stars
while drinking wine on the beach.

902
00:57:20,920 --> 00:57:21,840
Thank you.

903
00:57:22,960 --> 00:57:25,160
You are the only thing
that makes me smile.

904
00:57:25,760 --> 00:57:27,360
I really want to be with you.

905
00:57:28,320 --> 00:57:30,080
Don’t be so nice to me.

906
00:57:30,360 --> 00:57:32,080
How would I live without you?

907
00:57:32,120 --> 00:57:34,440
You will never live without me.

908
00:57:34,800 --> 00:57:35,640
Remember it.

909
00:57:36,440 --> 00:57:40,360
Miss Bambi said she doesn’t want to be
a burden to anyone.
